ways been baffled by these kinds of decisions, its like they aren't thinking of Wizards when they design things, we are left out of the loop entirely. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uapokkberzerk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Apokk Berzerk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/2/01 9:24:57 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://142.55.42.238/apokk_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Scars of Sigil 2 sec cast time !!! WHAT !?!?</span><hr size=1> yeah you might be right about that grim, but I don't think it's such a big deal. We aren't too bad at lvl 16 nonetheless, and besides, lvl 16 is a blink of an eye compared to an entire Wizard's career...i'm more worried about the higher lvls where the real problems lie, not that lower lvls aren't important, but as a whole, they aren't that bad.<br>
